Naadha Gama Nuwara Eliya yet again proved the young generation musicians of our country are versatile and so talented. The tickets for the show was sold out in 15 minutes once it went online which made the organisers to set up a extra day for those who couldn't grab a ticket. 

We had our fair share of excitement on the road trip up to the hills to get to Saturday's show. The atmosphere at the iconic Gregory Lake was simply breathtaking. The cold weather and light drizzle gave the spectators chills to go with the soothing music and dance moves. Despite the weather, the fans and artists dissapoint as the misty Gregory sang to the beats of the crowd. 

The organisers had done a tremendous job in setting up the place with nothing much to complain. The franchise has grown over the years and now have their own merchandise which proves that building a home grown brand is possible with sheer commitment and passion.Â  

I have been to a few of the shows now and rate this show, experience wise the best. This is certainly our version of various artists which you should experience at least once. There could be few more improvements which could make the experience even more better but Naadha Gama is here to stay. 

By Mafaz Mohideen
